.TH "LIGHTNING-CHANNEL-FORCE-CLOSE" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-channel-force-close \- force-close a channel unilaterally
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning channel-force-close
.I channel_id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Calls
.B lightning-cli close
with a timeout of 0 to trigger an immediate unilateral close.
Use only when the peer is unresponsive and a mutual close is impossible.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true,"type":..., "tx":...}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-close (1),
.BR lightning-channel-drain (1)
